Vue CLI - Creating our Project

step-1
install npm
->npm i -g @vue/cli

step-2
creat vue project
->vue create projectName

or

user vue ui command like
->vue ui


step-3
run the server with command
->npm run serve

step-4
application build process the following command will create dist folder
->npm run build


install VS Code plugin for vuejs like
vetur


# 1). project folder tour

    1. node_modules : all dependencies needed to build project
    2. public : put files you don't want run through webpak
    3. src : where all our application code goes
        i. asset : Store asset such as images, fonts...
        ii. components : Store building blocks of Vue application
        iii. Router: vue Router
        iv. store : vuex
        v. views : Store files for different "pages"

    project files
    App.vue : Root component
                - all other components are nested within
    main.js : Renders app and mounts to Dom

    How is the app being loaded?

# 3). Optimizaing and install VS Code  plugin like
    ESlint + prettier-code formatter + Vue VSCode Snippets


# 4). Vue Router Basics
    1. client side routing
        i. click a link 
            a). return page -> sends over HTML to render the different pages
            b). return page -> renders differences without reloading the page
            c). a web app that loads from a single page (index.html) and dynamically updates as
                the user interacts with the app.
    2. setting up vue Router
    3. name routes
    4. redirecting & aliasing
    5. building example app

